definition.value: A notoamide that is 7,7-dimethyl-1,7-dihydropyrano[2,3-g]indol-2(3H)-one which is substituted at position 3 by 3-methylbut-1-en-3-yl and [(3S,8aS)-1,4-dioxooctahydropyrrolo[1,2-a]pyrazin-3-yl]methyl groups (the all-S stereoisomer). Isolated from a mussel-derived Aspergillus species.

An organic heterohexacyclic compound isolated from a mussel-derived Aspergillus species that is 3,6b,7,7a,10,11,12,12a,14a,15-decahydro-8H,13H-pyrano[2,3-g]pyrrolo[1'',2'':4',5']pyrazino[1',2':1,5]pyrrolo[2,3-b]indole-8,13-dione which is substituted by two methyl groups at position 3, a hydroxy group at the 6b position, and a 2-methylbut-3-en-2-yl group at the 14a position (the 6bR, 7aS, 12aS, 14aS stereoisomer).
A 1-methyl-1-[1-oxo-1-(10H-phenothiazin-10-yl)propan-2-yl]pyrrolidinium that has R-configuration.
A 1-methyl-1-[1-oxo-1-(10H-phenothiazin-10-yl)propan-2-yl]pyrrolidinium that has S-configuration.
A member of the class of phenothiazines that is 10H-phenothiazine which is substituted by a 2-(1-methylpyrrolidin-1-ium-1-yl)propanoyl group at position 10.

Any member of the class of indole alkaloids isolated from a marine-derived Aspergillus fungus and derived from proline, tryptophan and one or two isoprene units. They are closely related to  brevianamides,  paraherquamides,  marcfortines,  asperparalines and stephacidins.
A methyl glycoside that is beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-[beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc-(1->6)]-beta-D-GlcNAc in which the hydroxy group at the reducing-end anomeric centre is methylated.

A methyl glycoside that is beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-[beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc-(1->6)]-beta-D-GlcNAc in which the CH2OH of the galactose within the trisaccharide chain is replaced by anionic carboxylate and the hydroxy group at the reducing-end anomeric centre is methylated.

An anthocyanin cation consisting of delphinidin having a rutinosyl [6-deoxy-alpha-L-mannosyl-(1->6)-beta-D-glucosyl] residue attached at the 3-hydroxy position and a beta-D-glucosyl residue at the 7-hydroxy position.
A conjugate base of delphinidin 3-O-rutinoside-7-O-beta-D-glucoside arising from selective deprotonation of the 5-hydroxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
A glycoside that is beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-[beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc-(1->6)]-beta-D-GlcNAc in which the hydroxy group at the reducing-end anomeric centre is replaced by a 3-azaniumylpropyl group.

A carboxylic ester resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of (2S)-3-hydroxy-2-phenylpropanoic acid with the hydroxy group of (3-endo)-8-(4-butoxybenzyl)-3-hydroxy-8-methyl-8-azoniabicyclo[3.2.1]octane. Its bromide salt is used as an  antispasmodic drug.
A pyridazinium ion that is pyridazin-1-ium which is substituted by a phenyl, amino and methoxy groups at positions 1, 4 and 6, respectively.
An organic cation resulting from the protonation of one of the nitrogens of pyridazine or its derivatives.
An amino sulfonic acid that is the 3-amino derivative of propanesulfonic acid.

A carboxylic ester resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of (2S)-3-hydroxy-2-phenylpropanoic acid with the hydroxy group of (2R,4S,5S,7s)-9-butyl-7-hydroxy-9-methyl-3-oxa-9-azoniatricyclo[3.3.1.0(2,4)]nonane.
A glycoside that is beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-[beta-D-GalA(-)-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc-(1->6)]-beta-D-GlcNAc in which the hydroxy group at the reducing-end anomeric centre is replaced by a 3-azaniumylpropyl group.

A methyl glycoside that is beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-[beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc-(1->6)]-beta-D-GlcNAc in which the hydroxy group at position 6 of the galactose residue linked to O-4 of the reducing end glucosyl residue is replaced by an ammoniumyl group and the hydroxy group at the reducing-end anomeric centre is methylated.

A methyl glycoside that is beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-[beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc-(1->6)]-beta-D-GlcNAc in which the CH2OH of the galactose within the trisaccharide chain is replaced by anionic carboxylate, the hydroxy group at position 6 of the galactose residue linked to O-4 of the reducing end glucosaminyl residue is replaced by an ammoniumyl group and the hydroxy group at the reducing-end anomeric centre is methylated.

A synthetic glucocorticoid resulting from the formal condensation of the 21-hydroxy group of prednisolone with one of the hydroxy groups of phosphoric acid. It is a prodrug for prednisolone that is activated in vivo by phosphatases.
A steroid phosphate oxoanion which is the dianion obtained by the deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of prednisolone phosphate.
A disaccharide having arabinose at the reducing end with a glycosyl residue attached at an unspecified position via a glycosidic bond.
Any glycoside derived from dimeric Lewis X {beta-D-Galp-(1->4)-[alpha-L-Fucp-(1->3)]-beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->3)-beta-D-Galp-(1->4)-[alpha-L-Fucp-(1->3)]-beta-D-GlcpNAc}.
A methyl glycoside that is alpha-L-Fucp-(1->3)-[beta-D-Galp-(1->4)]-beta-D-Glcp (LacLe(x)) in which the hydroxy group at the reducing-end anomeric centre is methylated.
A methyl glycoside that is alpha-L-Fucp-(1->3)-[beta-D-Glcp-(1->4)]-beta-D-GlcpNAc (Le(x)) in which the hydroxy group at the reducing-end anomeric centre is methylated.
An N-silyl compound that is silane in which a hydrogen is substituted by an amino group.
A monounsaturated fatty aldehyde that is heptadecanal carrying a double bond at position 16.
An N-acylglycine resulting from the formal condensation of the amino group of glycine with the carboxy group of trifluoroacetic acid.

A member of the class of quinolizines that is trans-5-methyloctahydro-2H-quinolizinium which is substituted by a di(thiophen-2-yl)methylidene group at position 3. Its bromide salt is used as an antispasmodic drug.
A primary alcohol that is hex-3-ene substituted by a hydroxy group at position 1.
A monohydroxyacetophenone that is acetophenone in which one of the hydrogens ortho to the acetyl group has been replaced by a hydroxy group.
A carboxylic ester resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of isobutyric acid with the 1-hydroxy group of 2,4,4-trimethylpentane-1,3-diol.
A methyl glycoside that is beta-D-Galp-(1->4)-[alpha-L-Rhap-(1->3)]-beta-D-GlcpNAc (LacLe(x)) in which the hydroxy group at the reducing-end anomeric centre is methylated.
A methyl glycoside that is beta-D-Galp-(1->4)-[alpha-L-Rhap-(1->3)]-beta-D-Glcp (RhaLac) in which the hydroxy group at the reducing-end anomeric centre is methylated.
A steroid acid that is 4beta,14-dimethyl-5alpha,9beta-9,19-cyclocholest-24-en-3beta-ol in which the 4alpha hydrogen has been replaced by a carboxy group.

A cyclic adenyl ribonucleotide that is cAMP (cyclic adenosine 3',5'-phosphate) in which the hydrogen at position 8 has been replaced by a piperidin-1-yl group. A selective cAMP-dependent protein kinase A (PKA) activator and cAMP analogue with high selectivity for site A of PKA type I and for site B of PKA type II.
An ammonium ion derivative that is the conjugate acid of (S)-methcathinone obtained from the protonation of the amino group. It is the major species at pH 7.3.
A monocarboxylic acid anion resulting from the deprotonation of the carboxy group of (Z)-3-amino-2-methylacrylic acid. The major species at pH 7.3.
A methylhypoxanthine that is hypoxanthine with the methyl group at position 9.
A methylhypoxanthine that is hypoxanthine with the methyl group at position 7.
A gamma-lactone that is oxolan-2-one substituted by a butyl group at position 5. It is a volatile compound found in peaches, mangoes, beef and ham.
A methylhypoxanthine that is hypoxanthine with the methyl group at position 3.
A gamma-lactone that is oxolan-2-one substituted by a hexyl group at position 5.
An alpha,beta-unsaturated monocarboxylic acid that is methacrylic acid (2-methylacrylic acid) in which the pro-Z hydrogen at the beta position has been replaced by an amino group.
